tion resonance our best\norbit fit is close to the stable solution previously identified for a\nthree-planet system, and involves low eccentricity for planet d (ed = 0.10) and\nmoderate inclination of the system (i = 28.0 deg), assuming a coplanar system,\ncircular orbits for b and c, and exact resonance with integer period ratios.\nUnder these assumptions, we can place strong constraints on the inclination of\nthe system (27.3 - 31.4 deg) and on the eccentricity for d ed < 0.46.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 6 Oct 2011 20:00:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-10-10"}
