cal excitation exists only if $n$\nis even and $K$ includes a nontrivial element of $O(n)/SO(n)$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 7 Oct 2011 10:23:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 19 Dec 2011 03:57:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-12-20"}
